HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 935
By Powers
A RESOLUTION to honor and commend Kelli Jo Wright upon her
receipt of the 2026 Campbell County Good
Scout Award.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should salute those
citizens who, through their extraordinary efforts, have distinguished themselves as community
leaders of whom we can all be proud; and
WHEREAS, one such noteworthy person is Kelli Jo Wright, who is being honored with
the 2026 Good Scout Award by Scouting America for her outstanding leadership in Campbell
County and her longstanding support and promotion of Scouting and youth development; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Wright will receive this prestigious award at the Campbell County
Good Scout Award Dinner on March 12, 2026, at the Ball Farm Event Center in LaFollette; and
WHEREAS, a lifelong resident of LaFollette, Kelli Jo Wright began her professional
career at the age of sixteen working at the Campbell County Board of Education Central Office,
and over the years, she has built a diverse and accomplished career spanning sales, marketing,
advertising, real estate, and international student education programs; and
WHEREAS, Mrs. Wright is widely known as the owner and publisher of The Volunteer
Times media, which she has published since 2002 in both print and digital formats, providing
community news and features to a broad audience and fostering civic engagement throughout
Campbell County and beyond; and
WHEREAS, her commitment to service is evident through her extensive volunteer
leadership, including nearly seventeen years as chair of the Campbell County Christmas
Parade, her role in founding and overseeing numerous community events and charitable
initiatives, and her longtime support of organizations benefiting children, families, and local
causes, including the Girl Scouts and other youth-focused programs; and
HJR0935
013218
- 1 -

WHEREAS, Kelli Jo Wright has also demonstrated a deep commitment to cultural
exchange and education, having personally hosted numerous international students in her
home and overseeing programs that have enabled students from around the world to attend
school in Campbell County, enriching the community through diversity and service; and
WHEREAS, guided by her faith, Kelli Jo Wright has long given of her time and talents in
support of faith-based and community ministries, including many years of service as a youth
ministry leader with churches in the LaFollette area, reflecting her commitment to service,
mentorship, and the well-being of young people; and
WHEREAS, her many accomplishments aside, Mrs. Wright is most grateful for the love
and support she shares with her husband of forty years, James Wright; their two daughters,
Karli Huguenard and Karmin Wright; and their grandson, Foster; and
WHEREAS, through her estimable service to Campbell County, Kelli Jo Wright
epitomizes the spirit of leadership, generosity, and commitment that are characteristic of a true
Tennessean; and
WHEREAS, we find it appropriate to acknowledge and applaud Mrs. Wright for her
dedication to her community, the State of Tennessee, and the ideals of Scouting; now,
therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and commend Kelli Jo Wright upon her receipt of the 2026
Campbell County Good Scout Award, thank her for her meritorious service to Campbell County
and this State, and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
